The final report by The People's Commission of Inquiry Into The Safety of Children tells stories of children's pain and grief. CAPE TOWN - The Western Cape is the most dangerous province in the country for children. Every week for the past five years, an average of four children have been killed and scores injured or attacked. READ: Hawks arrest orphanage manager for alleged child abuse The Cape Town Trauma Centre says after the provincial government refused to convene a judicial commission of inquiry into child safety, it decided to hold its own. It heard stories of rape, physical abuse, abductions, as well as child trafficking. More than a thousand children testified using art-based therapy. READ: Kids removed from WC facility following abuse allegations The most vulnerable victims include young girls and boys, undocumented refugee children and children with physical disabilities. This report has no legal standing but it's given a voice to many who would otherwise not have been heard.